Tie-Breaking finals:

[Feb 10, 1963]
Cruzeiro  1-0  Atlético

[Feb 13]
Atlético         2-1  Cruzeiro

[Feb 15]
Atlético         1-1  Cruzeiro                          (aet 1-0)
 [Dinar 55’; Rossi 20’]
 [Toninho 100’]

CAM: Marcial; Reginaldo, Willian, Procópio and Marcelino; 
Dinar and Fifi; Toninho, Nilson, Afonsinho and Noêmio
Coach: Antoninho.

CEC: Mussula; Massinha,Vavá, Dilsinho and Geraldino; 
Nuno and Rossi; Nerival, Dirceu Pantera, Nelsinho and Raimundinho (Emerson)
Coach: Niginho.

Atlético-MG were the Minas Gerais champion of 1962 and qualified to Taça Brasil 1963.

Topscorer: Marco Antônio (América), 21 goals.

